cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.DS

The paper discusses the properties of deep neural networks in the context of classification, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks in image classification, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper uses tools from compressed sensing and dictionary learning, which are related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the metric learning properties of the network, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
